snippet.textDisplay:
It's a conversation between Sohni and her clay pot, which is about to sink along her. She used to travel across river Chnaab each night to meet Mahiwaal, but one day that clay pot got replaced with the unbaked clay pot by her sister-in-law, who was jealous of Sohni.
So, in the middle of the river Sohni realized it's not her solid baked pot and she won't be able to cross the river to see Mahiwaal. 
She's drowning. . . " aj mahiwal nu me jana mil we- aaj milegi laash yaar di " Poetic Punjabi of Pakistan! 
Love you Coke studio for this surreal melody!
